Ancestral Aspirant		KEY:Occultist Archetype ~ Ancestral Aspirant						CATEGORY:Archetype		TYPE:Archetype.OccultistArchetype																								PRECLASS:1,Occultist=1		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Occultist Archetype ~ Ancestral Aspirant],[!PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Occultist_Archetype_ClassSkills=True,Occultist_Archetype_Implements=True,Occultist_Archetype_ObjectReading=True,Occultist_Archetype_OutsideContact=True]																																																																																										DESC:It is common for a noble to possess a deep pride for his family's past, but when such self-importance gives way to obsession, an ancestral aspirant is born. Ancestral aspirants perform all the typical social functions of a noble, but they fill their conversations with stories of the great deeds of their family forebears, and they spend their nights researching old histories and primary sources, hungry for more.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Ancestral Aspirant ~ Class Skills|PRECLASS:1,Occultist=1	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Ancestral Aspirant ~ Family Jewels|PRECLASS:1,Occultist=1	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Ancestral Aspirant ~ Emotional Reading|PRECLASS:1,Occultist=2	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Ancestral Aspirant ~ Courtly Contacts|PRECLASS:1,Occultist=8																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.67																																																																																											FACT:Occultist_Archetype_ClassSkills|true	FACT:Occultist_Archetype_Implements|true	FACT:Occultist_Archetype_ObjectReading|true	FACT:Occultist_Archetype_OutsideContact|true	FACT:Occultist_CF_ClassSkills|true	FACT:Occultist_CF_ObjectReading|true	FACT:Occultist_CF_OutsideContact|true
Secret Broker			KEY:Occultist Archetype ~ Secret Broker							CATEGORY:Archetype		TYPE:Archetype.OccultistArchetype																								PRECLASS:1,Occultist=1		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Occultist Archetype ~ Secret Broker],[!PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Occultist_Archetype_ClassSkills=True,Occultist_Archetype_Implements=True,Occultist_Archetype_ImplementMastery=True,Occultist_Archetype_MagicItemSkill=True,Occultist_Archetype_ShiftFocus=True,Occultist_Archetype_MagicCircles=True,Occultist_Archetype_BindingCircles=True,Occultist_Archetype_FastCircles=True]																																																																	DESC:Whether as spymasters, extortionists, political fixers, or puppet masters, secret brokers use their talents with objects to gain information, then leverage that information for their own purposes.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Secret Broker ~ Class Skills|PRECLASS:1,Occultist=1	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Secret Broker ~ Knowledge Is Power|PRECLASS:1,Occultist=1	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Secret Broker ~ Broker Secrets|PRECLASS:1,Occultist=2	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Secret Broker ~ Share Memory|PRECLASS:1,Occultist=4	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Secret Broker ~ Steal Secret|PRECLASS:1,Occultist=8	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Secret Broker ~ Erase Secret|PRECLASS:1,Occultist=12	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Secret Broker ~ Purge Secret|PRECLASS:1,Occultist=16																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.68																																																																																											FACT:Occultist_Archetype_ClassSkills|true	FACT:Occultist_Archetype_Implements|true	FACT:Occultist_Archetype_ImplementMastery|true	FACT:Occultist_Archetype_MagicItemSkill|true	FACT:Occultist_Archetype_ShiftFocus|true	FACT:Occultist_Archetype_MagicCircles|true	FACT:Occultist_Archetype_BindingCircles|true	FACT:Occultist_Archetype_FastCircles|true	FACT:Occultist_CF_MagicItemSkill|true	FACT:Occultist_CF_ShiftFocus|true	FACT:Occultist_CF_MagicCircles|true	FACT:Occultist_CF_BindingCircles|true	FACT:Occultist_CF_FastCircles|true

Class Skills			KEY:Ancestral Aspirant ~ Class Skills							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Occultist Class Features.AncestralAspirantClassFeatures																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												CSKILL:Appraise|Bluff|TYPE=Craft|Diplomacy|Disable Device|Disguise|Fly|Knowledge (arcana)|Knowledge (engineering)|Knowledge (history)|Knowledge (nobility)|Knowledge (religion)|Linguistics|Perception|Sense Motive|Sleight of Hand|Spellcraft|Use Magic Device													SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Family Jewels			KEY:Ancestral Aspirant ~ Family Jewels							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Occultist Class Features.AncestralAspirantClassFeatures.SpecialQuality																																																																																																																																																											DESC:An ancestral aspirant's implements are always objects connected to his family history. One of his starting implements must be an implement from the enchantment school. This ability alters implements.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Emotional Reading			KEY:Ancestral Aspirant ~ Emotional Reading						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Occultist Class Features.AncestralAspirantClassFeatures.SpecialQuality																																																																																																																																																											DESC:An ancestral aspirant doesn't care much about objects that didn't belong to his ancestors, but he is keenly attuned to his relatives and fellow nobles, allowing him to read the emotions of others. If he spends 1 minute examining a creature, he learns one fact, chosen by the GM, about the creature's current emotions. Since emotional auras are complex, this ability is unlikely to reveal the secret feelings of a professional spy; instead, it only touches upon surface emotions.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Courtly Contacts			KEY:Ancestral Aspirant ~ Courtly Contacts							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Occultist Class Features.AncestralAspirantClassFeatures.SpecialQuality																																																																																																																																																											DESC:Ancestral aspirants have contacts among courtly circles rather than otherworldly circles. This works similarly to outside contact except for the following differences; First, he doesn't need to use a magic circle or make a payment (though he still expends 1 point of mental focus from his enchantment implement). Second, he can use those contacts to gather information for him (as per the Diplomacy skill to gather information) without spending the time himself, rather than asking a question and receiving a result similar to a divination. He can ask more questions over the same time period as normal with outside contact, for a total of %1 questions that are in some way related to one another.|(OccultistLVL-4)/4	DESC: Instead of delivering messages and objects, the courtly contacts can spread vicious rumors and gossip about a target throughout a settlement, causing any creatures in the settlement whose attitude toward the target wasn't helpful to have its attitude toward the target worsened by one step. These baseless rumors last 1 week or until the target spends 8 hours refuting them and succeeds at a Diplomacy check (DC %1).|10+OccultistLVL+INT|PRECLASS:1,Occultist=16																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.68

Class Skills			KEY:Secret Broker ~ Class Skills								CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Occultist Class Features.SecretBrokerClassFeatures																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													CSKILL:Bluff|TYPE=Knowledge																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Knowledge Is Power		KEY:Secret Broker ~ Knowledge Is Power							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Occultist Class Features.SecretBrokerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality																																																																																																																																																												DESC:The secret broker starts play possessing a single divination implement, typically a ledger of secrets. She gains new implements as normal at 2nd level and every 4 levels thereafter, and they can be of any school. A secret broker's third eye resonant power grants an insight bonus on Profession and Sense Motive checks equal to the bonus it grants on Perception checks, and an insight bonus on all Knowledge checks equal to half that bonus. She must select divination with implement mastery. This ability alters implements and implement mastery.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Occultist Implement School ~ Divination																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Broker Secrets			KEY:Secret Broker ~ Broker Secrets								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Occultist Class Features.SecretBrokerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural																																																																																																																																																										DESC:A secret broker can trade her secrets to another. For the purpose of this ability, an object's secret is composed of pieces of information gained from a single object through object reading, object seer, psychometry, or read object that the occultist didn't otherwise know and hasn't shared with another, written somewhere, or otherwise recorded or found a way to recover should she forget them and lose possession of the object. The secret broker can willingly use this ability in tandem with handing the object over to another creature in order to transfer the object's secret to that creature. The secret broker forgets the object's secret and the creature instantly learns the object's secret. The secret broker can also destroy an object to remove his memory of the object's secret without transferring it to another. In either case, any onlookers who understand what the secret broker is doing, and the recipient in the case of a transfer, can intrinsically tell that the secret broker has used this ability rather than simply sharing the memory through other means or destroying the object but keeping its secret.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Share Memory			KEY:Secret Broker ~ Share Memory								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Occultist Class Features.SecretBrokerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.SpellLike																																																																																																																																															SPELLS:Innate|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=TL|Share Memory,12+INT	DESC:A secret broker learns to use her knowledge transference powers more flexibly, allowing her to use share memory at will, but only with willing targets.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Steal Secret			KEY:Secret Broker ~ Steal Secret								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Occultist Class Features.SecretBrokerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.SpellLike																																																																																																																																																										DESC:A secret broker learns how to steal a secret from an unwilling target. This works as her share memory ability, except it allows her to access memories from unwilling targets. A target that succeeds at its saving throw against a secret broker's steal secret ability is forever after immune to that secret broker's steal secret ability. While this ability replaces magic circles, the secret broker can still use outside contact, though she leverages the outsider's secrets rather than create a circle. It still takes 1 minute to call it (the same length of time it normally takes to draw the circle) and costs 2 points of mental focus, even though she isn't using magic circles.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Erase Secret			KEY:Secret Broker ~ Erase Secret								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Occultist Class Features.SecretBrokerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.SpellLike																																																																																																																																																										DESC:A secret broker can expend 1 point of mental focus from her divination implement in order to erase a fact from someone's mind by touch. This works similarly to modify memory to erase the memory of an event, except the effect is instantaneous and leaves no magical trace (it can still be removed by break enchantment, psychic surgery, limited wish, miracle, or wish) and the secret broker can remove only one fact, such as "The queen and the general are having an affair" rather than a 5-minute event. Erasing the memory of a fact does not prevent the target from learning the fact again, or even potentially from deducing the fact again from evidence, given time.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Purge Secret			KEY:Secret Broker ~ Purge Secret								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Occultist Class Features.SecretBrokerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.SpellLike																																																																																																																																																										DESC:A secret broker can expend 3 points of mental focus from her divination implement to apply her erase secret ability to up to %1 creatures within 30 feet of her.|OccultistLVL																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.69

